# grapher_aspect_small_circle_smoke.numos — Phase 10C. Plot y = x^2 + y^2, which
# is the circle x^2 + (y-0.5)^2 = 0.25 (radius 0.5, centre (0,0.5)) tangent to the
# x-axis at the origin. With equal-aspect rendering it must be a TRUE small circle
# touching the origin, not a squashed oval. Warning-only (screenshot, no golden).
log "aspect small circle: start"
wait 200
open_app Grapher
wait 60
key down
key enter
# Type "y=x^2+y^2"
key y
key =
key x
key ^
key 2
key right
key +
key y
key ^
key 2
key enter
wait 80
key graph
wait 80
key ac
key zoom
key zoom
key zoom
wait 150
screenshot out/grapher_aspect_small_circle_smoke.ppm
assert_app Grapher
log "aspect small circle: y=x^2+y^2 plotted"
